* ============================================================
* LIST_EXHAUSTIVE_CURSOR_ORDER_BASELINE_V1.DTS
*
* Purpose:
*   Baseline regression for LIST cursor/reporting + order behavior
*   before SMARTLIST changes.
*
* Scope:
*   - natural order
*   - ordered/CDX/LMDB-backed order where available
*   - cursor anchoring
*   - cursor restore behavior
*   - physical recno vs logical row reporting
*   - TOP/BOTTOM/SKIP/GO/LIST/LIST TOP/LIST BOTTOM/LIST ALL
*   - SET ORDER TO 0 / TAG ordering
*   - SET FILTER TO interactions
*   - FOR clause interactions
*   - DELETED visibility behavior
*   - zero-visible-row behavior
*   - duplicates in ordered keys
*
* Notes:
*   - LIST is the gold-standard reference for this phase.
*   - Do not change this script casually once you accept it.
*   - Use transcript diffing across builds.
* ============================================================

SET ECHO OFF
ECHO ===== LIST EXHAUSTIVE CURSOR ORDER BASELINE START =====

COLOR DEFAULT
VERSION
WSREPORT

* ------------------------------------------------------------
* SECTION 0: OPEN / SANITY
* ------------------------------------------------------------
ECHO ===== SECTION 0: OPEN / SANITY =====
SCHEMAS CLOSE
SCHEMAS OPEN DBF
STATUS
WSREPORT

* ------------------------------------------------------------
* SECTION 1: NATURAL ORDER / ROOMS
* area 9 in current sample set
* ------------------------------------------------------------
ECHO ===== SECTION 1: NATURAL ORDER / ROOMS =====
SELECT 9
AREA
FIELDS
COUNT
SET ORDER TO 0
TOP
LIST 5
LIST 5
SKIP 5
LIST 5
LIST 5
GO 1
LIST 5
BOTTOM
LIST 5
LIST TOP
LIST BOTTOM
LIST ALL
AREA
STATUS

* ------------------------------------------------------------
* SECTION 2: NATURAL ORDER / STUD_MAJ
* larger table, no ordered dependency
* ------------------------------------------------------------
ECHO ===== SECTION 2: NATURAL ORDER / STUD_MAJ =====
SELECT 10
AREA
FIELDS
COUNT
SET ORDER TO 0
TOP
LIST 5
LIST 5
SKIP 2
LIST 5
GO 1
LIST 5
BOTTOM
LIST 5
LIST TOP
LIST BOTTOM
LIST ALL
AREA
STATUS

* ------------------------------------------------------------
* SECTION 3: FILTER TO ZERO VISIBLE ROWS
* intentionally invalid field for this table shape
* ------------------------------------------------------------
ECHO ===== SECTION 3: FILTER TO ZERO VISIBLE ROWS =====
SELECT 9
SET ORDER TO 0
TOP
SET DELETED ON
SET FILTER TO MAJOR = "CS"
TOP
LIST 5
LIST 5
COUNT
SKIP 2
LIST 5
SET FILTER TO
TOP
LIST 5
AREA
STATUS

* ------------------------------------------------------------
* SECTION 4: FOR CLAUSE IN NATURAL ORDER
* use valid fields on ROOMS
* ------------------------------------------------------------
ECHO ===== SECTION 4: FOR CLAUSE / NATURAL ORDER =====
SELECT 9
SET ORDER TO 0
TOP
LIST FOR CAP > 50
TOP
LIST FOR BLDG = "BLDG03"
TOP
LIST 10 FOR ROOM = "BLDG04-1"
TOP
LIST ALL FOR CAP < 30
AREA
STATUS

* ------------------------------------------------------------
* SECTION 5: ORDERED STREAM / STUDENTS LNAME
* area 11 in current sample set
* this is the critical ordered baseline
* ------------------------------------------------------------
ECHO ===== SECTION 5: ORDERED STREAM / STUDENTS LNAME =====
SELECT 11
AREA
FIELDS
COUNT
SET ORDER TO TAG LNAME
AREA
TOP
LIST 5
LIST 5
SKIP 5
LIST 5
LIST 5
TOP
LIST 5
BOTTOM
LIST 5
LIST TOP
LIST BOTTOM
LIST ALL
AREA
STATUS

* ------------------------------------------------------------
* SECTION 6: ORDERED STREAM / SEEK ANCHORING
* prove LIST honors current cursor after ordered nav
* ------------------------------------------------------------
ECHO ===== SECTION 6: ORDERED SEEK ANCHORING =====
SELECT 11
SET ORDER TO TAG LNAME
TOP
SEEK "ANDERSON"
LIST 5
LIST 5
SKIP 1
LIST 5 
SEEK "BROWN"
LIST 5
SEEK "CLARK"
LIST 5
SEEK "DAVIS"
LIST 5
AREA
STATUS

* ------------------------------------------------------------
* SECTION 7: ORDERED STREAM / DUPLICATE KEY ZONE
* exercise same-key cluster behavior
* ------------------------------------------------------------
ECHO ===== SECTION 7: ORDERED DUPLICATE KEY ZONE =====
SELECT 11
SET ORDER TO TAG LNAME
SEEK "ANDERSON"
LIST 5
SKIP 1
LIST 5
SKIP 1
LIST 5
SKIP 1
LIST 5
SKIP 1
LIST 5
SKIP 1
LIST 5
TOP
LIST 5
AREA
STATUS

* ------------------------------------------------------------
* SECTION 8: ORDERED + FOR
* exercise ordered stream with classic FOR predicates
* ------------------------------------------------------------
ECHO ===== SECTION 8: ORDERED + FOR =====
SELECT 11
SET ORDER TO TAG LNAME
TOP
LIST FOR LNAME = "ANDERSON"
TOP
LIST 10 FOR MAJOR = "CSCI"
TOP
LIST ALL FOR GENDER = "F"
SEEK "CLARK"
LIST FOR LNAME = "CLARK"
AREA
STATUS

* ------------------------------------------------------------
* SECTION 9: ORDERED + SET FILTER TO
* visible stream under active order
* ------------------------------------------------------------
ECHO ===== SECTION 9: ORDERED + SET FILTER TO =====
SELECT 11
SET ORDER TO TAG LNAME
SET FILTER TO LNAME = "CLARK"
TOP
LIST 5
LIST 5
SKIP 2
LIST 5
COUNT
SET FILTER TO
TOP
LIST 5
AREA
STATUS

* ------------------------------------------------------------
* SECTION 10: ORDER RESET / PHYSICAL RETURN
* prove SET ORDER TO 0 reverts stream semantics
* ------------------------------------------------------------
ECHO ===== SECTION 10: ORDER RESET / PHYSICAL RETURN =====
SELECT 11
SET ORDER TO TAG LNAME
TOP
LIST 5
SET ORDER TO 0
TOP
LIST 5
SKIP 5
LIST 5
AREA
STATUS

* ------------------------------------------------------------
* SECTION 11: DESCENDING ORDER
* only if your active tag/order infrastructure honors DESC here
* if DESC command differs in your build, adjust accordingly
* ------------------------------------------------------------
ECHO ===== SECTION 11: DESCENDING ORDER =====
SELECT 11
SET ORDER TO TAG LNAME DESCEND
AREA
TOP
LIST 5
SKIP 5
LIST 5
BOTTOM
LIST 5
LIST TOP
LIST BOTTOM
SET ORDER TO TAG LNAME ASCEND
TOP
LIST
AREA
STATUS

* ------------------------------------------------------------
* SECTION 12: CROSS-AREA CURSOR SANITY
* confirms cursor line area numbering remains stable
* ------------------------------------------------------------
ECHO ===== SECTION 12: CROSS-AREA CURSOR SANITY =====
SELECT 9
TOP
LIST 5
SELECT 10
TOP
LIST 5
SELECT 11
SET ORDER TO TAG LNAME
TOP
LIST 5
SELECT 2
SET ORDER TO 0
TOP
LIST 5
STATUS

* ------------------------------------------------------------
* SECTION 13: EMPTY / EDGE TABLES IF PRESENT
* safe probes only; adjust area numbers if needed in your set
* ------------------------------------------------------------
ECHO ===== SECTION 13: EDGE TABLE PROBES =====
SELECT 5
AREA
COUNT
TOP
LIST 5
LIST ALL
STATUS

SELECT 6
AREA
COUNT
TOP
LIST 5
LIST ALL
STATUS

SELECT 7
AREA
COUNT
TOP
LIST
LIST ALL
STATUS

* ------------------------------------------------------------
* SECTION 14: FINAL RESTORATION
* leave system in predictable state
* ------------------------------------------------------------
ECHO ===== SECTION 14: FINAL RESTORATION =====
SELECT 11
SET FILTER TO
SET ORDER TO 0
TOP
AREA
STATUS
WSREPORT

ECHO ===== LIST EXHAUSTIVE CURSOR ORDER BASELINE END =====